  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nWe currently have two different ways of getting configuration params in both projects, the beacon chain uses params.GetConfig() while the validator uses params.DemoConfig() or params.DefaultConfig(). This is a bit confusing and would be best if we just stick to the way the beacon chain does so. This obfuscates what type of config parameters the system is using and lets the cli and node handle this effectively through a flag. This is preferred.\r\n\r\nA PR to close this would change validator's params package to match the way the beacon-chain handles its params.",
